race.comment: Not a deep form race to close the card. BETA BETTER (8) has raced twice this prep, both times over 1200m, and failed to make an impression. Crying out for this sort of distance at this stage of the campaign. Good enough to turn things around in moderate company. GIAPPONESE (6) easily won his maiden here over 1400m two back. Outclassed last start in the Group 3 Grand Prix at Eagle Farm. Back in his right grade today so keep him in calculations. The lightly raced SPICY WINGS (2) appreciated the step up in distance and took out his maiden recently over 1550m at Murwillumbah. In good hands so further improvement looks assured. Veteran MAGIC IN ME (4) hasn't won in ages but he cannot be ruled out coming back to a BM58. Hard to make a case for the rest, with GIDDY GAN'S JOY (5) coming off a two-month break probably the pick of them.
